AIM:
    To design a microcantilever biosensor and analyze its deflection due to applied surface stress.
SOFTWARE REQUIRED:
    COMSOL Multiphysics
PROCEDURE:
  Model Wizard:
    Select 3D
    Physics → Solid Mechanics
    Study → Stationary
    Click Done
GEOMETRY 1
  Set unit = µm
BLOCK (CANTILEVER)
    Length = 200 µm
    Width = 50 µm
    Thickness = 5 µm
    Build All
MATERIALS
    Add → Silicon
SOLID MECHANICS
  FIXED CONSTRAINT
    Select one end of cantilever → Fixed
  BOUNDARY LOAD / SURFACE STRESS
    Apply load on top surface
    Example: 0.1 N/m (surface stress)
MESH
    Free Tetrahedral → Build Mesh
STUDY
    Compute
RESULT:
    The deflection of the microcantilever due to applied surface stress is successfully obtained.
